President Obama has nominated Claire R. Kelly to serve on the United States Court of International Trade. Kelly is currently a Professor of Law at Brooklyn Law School, specializing in international trade and financial law. She is also involved in various organizations related to customs and international trade. Prior to her career in academia, Kelly worked as an associate at Coudert Brothers in New York City. She holds a J.D. magna cum laude from Brooklyn Law School and a B.A. cum laude from Barnard College.